<HEADLINE> West African Airlines to Take off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The West African Airlines, or ECOAIR,
will take off soon with a fleet of five aircraft at the first
place including Boeing 737s, an airline official said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to ECOAIR project co-ordinator Yemisi Olusola,
subscribers to the shares of the airlines are to hold their
inaugural meeting on July 22 in Abuja, capital of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The allocation of equity shares is in the ratio of 77 percent
to the West African private sector, 5 percent to existing national
carriers, some 8 percent to financial institutions and 10 percent
to technical partners, he said.
</P>
<P>
ECOAIR is considered as a key effort of the Economic Community
of West African States to achieve free movement of people and
goods within West Africa and between the sub-regions in the
African continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
