<HEADLINE> China Donates Equipment to S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at the handing-over ceremony in the capital Freetown
on behalf of the Sierra Leone government, Minister of Education,
Youths and Sports Amadu Wurie said the donation by the Chinese
government to Sierra Leone in such a difficult time once again
showed the sincere friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Wurie said his government would take the occasion to express
its gratitude to the government and people of China for their
selfless assistance.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic tie in 1971, China has
provided valued support and immense assistance to Sierra Leone in
many fields, the minister said, stressing that the bilateral
relationship between the two countries has gone beyond friendship
and become a family.
</P>
<P>
At the function, Yu Wuzhen, Chinese Ambassador to Sierra Leone,
said that the Chinese government and people has always supported
the efforts by the Sierra Leone government to realize lasting
peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He expressed optimism that the Sierra Leone government, under
the leadership of President Ahmad Tejan Kabbah, will overcome the
difficulties facing the country and maintain peace and development.
</P>
