<HEADLINE> Rwandese Officials Injured in Road Crash in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Four senior Rwandese government
officials, part of President Paul Kagame's delegation to Kenya,
were injured in a road accident as they raced to the State House,
Nairobi on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Their driver, a Kenyan attached to the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs, was also injured in the accident along the road leading
to the downtown from the airport.
</P>
<P>
The Mercedes Benz, carrying two Permanent Secretaries and two
parastatal chiefs from Rwanda, rammed into a truck when racing to
catch up with the limousine carrying Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi and Kagame.
</P>
<P>
Those injured were taken to hospital immediately and two of
them were later discharged.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the accident occurred due to a security lapse.
The driver of the truck, who had stopped along a feeder road,
drove into the highway just after the motorcade passed.
</P>
<P>
However, Deputy Traffic Commandant Solomon Kuria said that
investigations will unearth the cause of the accident.
</P>
<P>
Kagame and his delegation arrived here Friday morning over
bilateral cooperation and regional issues. 
</P>
