<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda, Uganda Youths Vow to Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan and Ugandan youths
have vowed to strengthen their traditional ties and fight all
forms of divisionism, Rwanda News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Attending a meeting in the Ugandan capital Kampala, youth
representatives from both countries stressed the need to fight all
poor political ideologies that promote conflicts in the two
countries and the Great Lakes Region as a whole.
</P>
<P>
They also showed their commitment to fight the deadly disease
AIDS, which has claimed a big number of youths hence retarding
development.
</P>
<P>
The Rwanda-Uganda youths conference came after the two heads of
state met to discuss way and means of consolidating the bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have strengthened their relations after the
recent clashes between the two armies in Kisangani city of the
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) causing heavy losses on
both civilians and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Rwanda, former allies in the DRC conflict, had been
supporting rebels fighting to topple the administration of DRC
President Laurent Kabila. However, their relations became
deteriorated as they decided to back rival factions of the rebels
last May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
