<DOCNO> XIE20000715.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Solidarity Within OPEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Saturday called on member
countries of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
(OPEC) to strengthen their solidarity and avoid influences from
outside.
</P>
<P>
OPEC countries must be strong and firm and exercise solidarity
in order to keep oil price and output at a justifiable level,
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami told visiting Venezuelan Oil
Minister Ali Rodriguez and head of the Venezuelan Presidential
Commission Jose Valero.
</P>
<P>
Khatami warned that some countries outside the organization have
a plot to widen the gap between oil supply and demand, so all OPEC
members should support the consensus and decisions made within the
group to avoid being influenced by outsiders.
</P>
<P>
"I believe there are hands at work to prepare the ground for
tilting the balance between supply and demand, hence inflicting
irreparable damage on oil producers through sudden fall in the
price," Khatami was quoted by the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) as saying.
</P>
<P>
He added that OPEC members must counter the "politically
motivated" plot through solidarity so that oil production and price
could be kept at a justifiable level.
</P>
<P>
Khatami also reiterated Iran's support for all OPEC strategies,
expressing hope that consolidation of the member countries would
ensure stable and fixed oil prices, which is beneficial to both
producing and consuming countries.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting, the Iranian president thanked Venezuelan
President Hugo Chavez for inviting him to attend the OPEC summit to
be held in the Venezuelan capital of Caracas in September. He said
the summit should open new horizon for stabilizing oil price, thus
serving the economic progress of member states.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan officials, who arrived here Saturday to
coordinate stances on the holding of the OPEC summit, also met with
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi, IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting, Kharrazi said oil price rises in the world
market are transitory and mainly caused by psychological propaganda
and the stock market. He said the OPEC should adopt long-term
decisions and regulate oil supply in line with market requirements.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister also called for closer cooperation between
Venezuela and Iran in the energy sector to help OPEC's standing
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Rodriguez, currently the OPEC president, held
separate talks with his Iranian counterpart Bijan Namdar Zanganeh.
</P>
<P>
Both officials stressed that the current high price level is
mainly attributed to market perception and speculation and logistic
problems, and that production increases by the OPEC actually cannot
solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
The international demands are mainly sweet and light (low
sulfur) crude, while additional supplies of crude oil from OPEC
member countries will continue to be on the side of heavy and sour
(high sulfur) crude, Rodriguez and Zanganeh noted.
</P>
<P>
This has resulted in the widening of the differentials between
sweet and sour crude, a problem that can not be solved by OPEC,
they added.
</P>
<P>
They praised the collective adherence of OPEC member states to
their decisions and promised to guarantee full commitment to all
agreements, including the one adopted at their ministerial meeting
in Vienna in June, which resulted in a collective output increase
of 708,000 barrels per day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
