<HEADLINE> McGrady to Sign Contract with Orlando Magic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Free agent Tracy McGrady, who
was courted by three NBA teams in the past week, said Friday that
he is choosing the Orlando Magic because he wants to play close to
home.
</P>
<P>
"Not too many superstars get a chance to play at home, and I
just saw myself taking advantage of it," McGrady said at the
Disney Wide World of Sports Complex, Florida where he works out.
</P>
<P>
The native of Auburndale, Florida, about 40 miles southwest of
Orlando, will likely sign a six-year deal worth 67.5 million US
dollars until August 1.
</P>
<P>
McGrady averaged 15.4 points and 6.3 rebounds last season with
the Toronto Raptors.
</P>
<P>
He said free agent forward Grant Hill's commitment to the Magic
earlier this month was a crucial factor in his decision.
</P>
<P>
"I think we're capable of turning this organization around in
the right way," said McGrady, 21, "I like their style of play and
I think my talent, to the team, just helps it out a lot."
</P>
<P>
McGrady also said he likes the style of Orlando coach Doc
Rivers, the NBA's coach of the year last season.
</P>
<P>
"I think Doc is a player's coach," he said, "For a young guy as
myself, you need guys like that who really care about you."
</P>
</TEXT>
