<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, DPRK Hold Session on Border River Shipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The 39th session of the China-
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) joint committee for
shipping on their border rivers closed here today.
</P>
<P>
During the 10-day event, the committee discussed last year's
work and the plan for 2000 in a friendly atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reached an agreement on issues of setting up and
maintaining the navigation points, navigational safety, and
dredging.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed on principle to open the cargo shipping
between China's Dandong port and the Sin'uiju port of the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, an annual event hosted alternately by the two
sides, is held in accordance with a bilateral agreement between
the two governments on the issue of border river shipping.
</P>
</TEXT>
