<HEADLINE> Iran Test-Fires Shahab-3 Missile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Saturday successfully test-
fired an upgraded Shahab-3 missile, the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The missile, with a range of about 1,280 kilometers, was test-
fired to ensure its conformity with the latest technological
standards, an informed source at the Defense Ministry was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, this was the second time that the
Shahab-3 missile had been tested.
</P>
<P>
The unnamed source said the missile has been developed for
defense purposes and poses no threat to any other country.
</P>
<P>
The Shahab-3 missile is said to be an improved model of North
Korea's Nodong-1. Iran conducted the first test of the missile in
1998. 
</P>
