<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Professors, Students Call for Ban on Fundamentalist Political Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Different student organizations and
distinguished professors Saturday urged the government to impose
ban on political activities of all fundamentalist political groups
including Jamaat-e-Islami and Islami Chhatra Shibir (Islamic
Students' Front) following their alleged involvement in Chittagong
massacre.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, five mid-ranking Bangladesh Chhatra League (
Bangladesh Students' League) leaders and two drivers were shot
dead in Chittagong by a group of gunmen of Islami Chhatra Shibir (
ICS), the student front of the Islamic fundamentalist Jamaat-e-
Islami.
</P>
<P>
Distinguished academician Professor Sirajul Islam Chowdhury of
Dhaka University termed the gruesome killings as one of the most
heinous incidents, saying the authorities should uproot their
unholy foundation and search for the root of their strength.
</P>
<P>
They should be dealt with iron hands and the civil society
should launch severe protest against the gruesome killings, the
professor stressed.
</P>
<P>
Strongly condemning the Chittagong massacre, President of
Samajtantrik Chhatra Front (Socialist Students' Front) Nurul Islam
in a statement said all religion-based political groups and
parties including Jammat-e-Islami and the ICS should be banned
immediately.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL) held a protest rally at Dhaka
University Saturday to protest against Wednesday's Chittagong
carnage, calling upon the pro-liberation progressive forces to
forge a strong resistance against the fundamentalist groups.
</P>
<P>
"They are misleading the people in the name of religion and
using religion to advance their petty party interest," the BCL
leaders said at the rally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
