<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Southwestern Airlines Starts New Air Route to ROK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China Southwestern Airlines
today started a new air route from Chongqing to Seoul of the
Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
It is the first direct flight ever operated by a Chinese air
company from southwest China to ROK. Asiana Airlines of ROK
launched flights from Seoul to Chongqing last month.
</P>
<P>
Return flights will be available every Wednesday and Saturday.
Boeing 737-800 planes will be used to fly the new route, with each
flight taking up three and a half hours.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials of Chongqing predict that ROK will become
another popular tourism destination after southeast Asian
countries for local residents.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 70 flights connecting Chongqing with 50
other Chinese cities and overseas destinations like Hong Kong,
Macao, Nagoya, Thailand, Munich.
</P>
<P>
To cater to the demand of developing west China, Chongqing will
spend 1.5 billion yuan to upgrade Jiangbei International Airport
into the biggest airport in southhwest China, according to a local
official. 
