<HEADLINE> Silver Prices Rise Smartly on Good Buying in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Prices of silver rose smartly on
the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) Saturday due to good
industrial buying coupled with higher overseas advices, while gold
improved further on increased local demand.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) resumed higher at 7,990 rupees (
181.59 U.S. dollars) per kilogram and rose further sharply to end
at 8,020 rupees (182.27 dollars), showing a good rise of 45 rupees
(1.02 dollars) over the last close of 7,975 rupees (181.25 dollars)
.
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) firmed up by 35 rupees (0.80 dollar)
to 7,895 rupees (179.43 dollars) per kg. from 7,860 rupees (178.63
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold both
improved further by 5 rupees (0.11 dollar) each to 4,515 rupees (
102.62 dollars) and 4,175 rupees (94.89 dollars) per 10 grams,
respectively, from 4,510 rupees (102.51 dollars) and 4,170 rupees
(94.78 dollars) Friday. 
</P>
