Campaign to have customers nominate the best staff at eight major
shopping malls in Hong Kong was launched by the Hong Kong Tourist
Association (HKTA) Saturday.
</P>
<P>
As part of the annual "Be A Good Host" campaign, the Super
Staff Election that will run through July and August aims to
encourage service staff to be courteous to customers and instill a
sense of pride in their work.
</P>
<P>
Those staff members with the most votes will be winners of the
election and will receive special awards from the HKTA.
</P>
<P>
Besides Super Staff Election, the "Be A Good Host" campaign
includes Comic Strip Creation Competition, E-Card Design
Competition and "Know Hong Kong" Competition, which are all aimed
to remind Hong Kong people to be good host to visitors to
consolidate Hong Kong's position as the most popular travel
destination in Asia.  
</P>
