<HEADLINE> DPRK Hails Establishment of Diplomatic Ties With Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The establishment of diplomatic
relations between the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
and the Philippines was prompted by the aspiration of the two
peoples to forge and develop friendly ties between the two
countries, a DPRK Foreign Ministry spokesman said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The setting-up of the ambassadorial level ties on the principle
of mutual respect for sovereignty, equality and reciprocity, has
created favorable conditions and circumstances not only for
developing bilateral relations but making positive joint efforts
for peace, prosperity, reconciliation and cooperation in the Asia-
Pacific region, the spokesman told the Korean Central News Agency.
</P>
<P>
It is the invariable stand of the DPRK government to establish
and upgrade friendly and cooperative relations with all the
countries that respect the sovereignty of the DPRK and are
friendly toward it, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK formally established diplomatic relations with the
Philippines by signing a joint communique on July 12 in Manila,
capital of the Philippines, after it opened ties with Italy and
Australia in last January and May respectively. 
</P>
