<HEADLINE> HK Youth Ambassadors to Make Overseas Visits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Commission on Youth of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region will sponsor 70 youth
ambassadors under an international exchange program to visit the
United Kingdom, Japan and Australia during the summer vacation and
early next year.
</P>
<P>
The visits aim at broadening these young people's horizon and
extending Hong Kong's goodwill overseas, said Chairman of the Sub-
Committee of the International Youth Exchange Program, Cheng Yan-
kee, at a press conference Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The Commission believes that young people can always learn
more from meeting people of different cultural background in their
daily life," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassadors, aged 18 to 24, are chosen from nearly 200
nominees from tertiary institutions, youth organizations and
government departments.
</P>
<P>
They will attend a series of briefings organized by the Home
Affairs Bureau and the commission to further enhance their general
knowledge and prepare a presentation on Hong Kong to be made
overseas, Cheng said. 
