<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Highlights of Diplomatic News (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China Urges U.S. to Abandon NMD Plan, FM Spokesman
</P>
<P>
China urges the United States to abandon the National Missile
Defense (NMD) system plan at an earliest time, Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sun was responding to a question about the failure of missile
defense system tests conducted by the U.S. recently.
</P>
<P>
China to Continue Cooperation with WB
</P>
<P>
China will continue its cooperation with the World Bank (WB)
despite the recent bank loan dispute, Sun said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that China and the WB have achieved success in 32
poverty-relief projects over the past years, and quality of the
projects has seen constant improvement.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman pointed out that the Chinese Government will
stick to and safeguard the WB principles, and spare no effort to
push forward the socio-economic development along with other
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
 China Regret over WB Decision
</P>
<P>
Sun Tuesday afternoon expressed regret for a recent decision
made by the World Bank (WB) to reject approval of a poverty
reduction project in a remote Chinese province.
</P>
<P>
Shareholders from developed members of the WB on July 8
rejected the recommendations of the Management of the World Bank
on the Qinghai Component of the China Western Poverty Reduction
Project.
</P>
<P>
 South China Sea Disputes not to be Complicated
</P>
<P>
The key to the South China Sea disputes is to avoid
complicating the issue, otherwise it will be harmful to regional
stability, FM spokesman Zhu Bangzao said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told a press conference that China has always insisted on
finding solutions to disputes with countries concerned through
friendly bilateral consultations and peaceful means, and progress
has been made in such consultations.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese FM to Attend ASEAN Meeting
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan of
Thailand, current chair of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN), Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan will attend
the first Foreign Ministers' Meeting of ASEAN-China, Japan, the
Republic of Korea (ROK) (10+3), the seventh Foreign Ministers'
Meeting of ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF), the thirty-third Foreign
Ministers' Meeting of Post Ministerial Conferences (PMC), and
ASEAN-China Dialogue Meeting (10+1) in Thailand from July 26 to 29,
Zhu announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
 Taiwan Doomed to Failure in UN Entry
</P>
<P>
Taiwan is doomed to failure in its effort to enter the United
Nations whatever tricks it will play, FM spokesman Zhu said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As a province of China, Taiwan has no qualification to enter
this international organization, Zhu stressed at a regular press
conference.
</P>
<P>
 China Self-Reliant on National Defense
</P>
<P>
China has relied on itself to enhance its power of national
defense and has also cooperated in some areas with a number of
friendly countries in this regard, Zhu said Thursday in response
to a question on Israel's cancellation of selling airborne warning
system to China.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out, no country has the right to interfere
with the bilateral cooperation between China and other countries.
</P>
