Egyptian pounds (6.6 billion U.S. dollars) in the the fiscal year
1999/2000, an increase of 4 billion pounds (1.15 billion dollars)
from that of the previous year, said Department Chairman Talaat
Hamad. It is a big leap although the market suffered from recession
and shortage of liquidity, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Mail:
</P>
<P>
-- Weather experts expect that Egypt's longest heat wave this
summer will end Saturday. For 12 days, soaring temperatures and
high humidity ganged up against people who gasped for a breath of
fresh air but to no avail. At pains to avoid long exposure to the
sun, people, particularly women, unfurled their umbrellas out on
the streets. Others improvised protection from the blazing sun by
covering their heads with whatever close at hand - a newspaper or a
piece of cardboard. 
