<P>
TOKYO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A powerful earthquake measuring 6.2
on the Richter scale jolted Niijima Island and nearby islands
south of Tokyo on Saturday morning, injuring two people and
causing landslides, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The two people suffered minor injuries in the quake, which
occurred at 10.30 a.m. (0130 GMT), the agency said, adding that
several landslides were observed on the islands, and 700
households suffered power cuts. (Japan-Quake)
