<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Politically Correct, Clear-Headed Young, Middle- aged Cadres (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Young and middle-aged cadres who
can withstand severe tests and stay clear-headed in major
struggles and crises should be promoted to leading positions,
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said recently.
</P>
<P>
They should also be able to mobilize and lead the masses to
surmount the difficulties, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the CPC Central
Committee, made the call on June 9 in an address at the national
conference of Party schools, which is to be published in the
leading Chinese magazine Seeking Truth on July 16.
</P>
<P>
In the building of the Party, priority should be given to
improving the ideological and political quality of leading Party
officials, especially the young and middle-aged ones, so that they
will become a new generation of politicians who are loyal to
Marxism, adhere to the socialist road with China's characteristics,
and are capable of running the Party and the State, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"The young and middle-aged officials are the hope of the Party
and the nation," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He strengthened education on the nature of the Party for the
young and middle-aged cadres so as to help them adhere to the
fundamental principle of devoting themselves to the people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000715.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Politically Correct, Clear-Headed Young, Middle- aged Cadres (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They should be open-minded so as to be good at judging the
general trends of the world's development and correctly assess the
demands of the time, he said.
</P>
<P>
They should be trained to think strategically so that they can
resolve major problems in reform, development and stability in a
realistic way, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
In general, their understanding of Marxism should be largely
improved to help them master Marxist positions, viewpoints and
approaches, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The top Party leader stressed that three points should be
considered during the selection of leading officials:
</P>
<P>
-- People should be selected based on their strong points;
</P>
<P>
-- People with fine quality and development potential should be
timely selected and carefully fostered by giving them proper
leading positions;
</P>
<P>
-- The Party's cause is great and needs talented professionals
of various kinds.  
