<HEADLINE> 2 Shot Dead at Mass Wedding in Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A gunman of a Palestinian tribe broke
into a mass wedding here Friday evening, shot dead a member of a
rival tribe before he was killed by police guarding the gathering,
police sources said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The gunman, identified as Khalid Ghizawi, was believed to be
revenging Saeed Harazeen, a guest at the mass wedding of some 70
Muslim couples on the campus of the Al-Itihad high school in the
north-western Sport City area of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Harazeen, then chatting with friends at the party, died after he
was shot five times into the chest before policemen on duty
returned fire and killed the attacker, causing panic among a crowd
of some 5,000 people at the campus party.
</P>
<P>
The party was cancelled and none of the brides and bridegrooms
sustained injuries.
</P>
<P>
Ghizawi killed Harazeen in retaliation for the recent killing of
a relative by Harazeen's tribe and he bore no intention to sabotage
the mass wedding, according to preliminary police investigations.
</P>
<P>
The two, from Palestinian families of the Gaza Strip in the West
Bank, had lived in Jordan's Gaza refugee camp for Palestinians
before the shooting incident on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
