<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Decline in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A total of 186,580 foreign tourists arrived in Sri Lanka in the
first five months of this year, a decrease of 1.5 percent from the
same period of last year, according to the Board.
</P>
<P>
During the month of May, a total of 23,404 tourists arrived as
against 25,212 in the same period in 1999, recording a decrease of
7.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
To increase tourist arrivals, the government is launching a 10
million U.S. dollar tourism campaign to sell and promote the
country's varied attractions in the world tourism market, tourist
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The government approved five million U.S. dollars for the
campaign in March this year. The balance is to be contributed by
the tourist board.
</P>
<P>
The government has appointed a special Marketing Advisory
Committee to draw up an extensive marketing strategy to boost the
national image and market Sri Lanka as an attractive tourist
destination, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka recorded 436,440 tourist arrivals last year, an
increase of 14.5 percent over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
