<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprise Resource Management Application Market Expected to Expand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Worldwide sales of enterprise
resource management applications are expected to grow from 14.5
billion U.S. dollars last year to 24.8 billion dollars in 2004,
according to a report released Friday.
</P>
<P>
This market will be fueled by organizations, especially midsize
companies, that want to reduce the task of integrating, operating
and maintaining multiple standalone applications, said the report
from U.S. market research firm International Data Corporation (IDC)
.
</P>
<P>
The rapid creation of smaller companies, driven by the internet
economy, the IDC said, will continue to drive growth of the market,
which includes accounting, human resource management and payroll,
and materials management applications. Accounting is and will
remain the largest segment, and materials management applications
will be the fastest-growing market, the IDC added.
</P>
<P>
"The Internet and e-commerce will be the growth engine for the
materials management software market for a number of years to come,
" said the report. "The multitude of new Internet companies
involved in business-to-business and business-to-consumer sales
has heated up demand for sophisticated new order fulfillment
software."
</P>
<P>
According to the IDC, North America will account for more than
half of the worldwide enterprise resource management application
market's revenues throughout the forecast. But the Middle East and
Eastern Europe will be the fastest-growing regions of the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
