<HEADLINE> Fostering of Young, Middle-aged Leading Cadres a Strategy of Communist Party: Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Constant fostering of young and
middle-aged leading cadres has always been a strategic task for
the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
made the remark June 9 in an address at the national conference of
Party schools, which is to be published by a leading Chinese
magazine Seeking Truth on July 16.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang urged that people recognize the importance
of fostering a large group of young and middle-aged leading Party
cadres who can handle the demands of the new century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang attacked the hegemony and power politics now evident in
the world, saying there's a long way to go before a multi-
polarized world can be achieved, as the United States has been
extraordinarily powerful in economic, science and technology, and
military fields.
</P>
<P>
He described the ongoing economic globalization as an "
objective process with dual nature."
</P>
<P>
The status of developing countries may be further weakened if
no correct countermeasures are taken when the developed western
countries are attempting to take the lead in the economic
globalization, according to Jiang, who is also Chinese president
and chairman of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000715.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fostering of Young, Middle-aged Leading Cadres a Strategy of Communist Party: Jiang (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang went on to point out that Chinese people should firmly
seize the opportunity to accelerate the country's development and
resolutely safeguard the country's interest and security.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the socialist modernization drive in China is to
enter into a new stage, Jiang said, stressing that China's general
goal is to basically realize socialist modernization and the great
reinvigoration of the Chinese nation by the mid-21st century.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is in a crucial period of transition between the elder
and younger generations of cadres, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Without a large number of leading officials who have both
ability and political integrity, it will be impossible for the
Party to rule the big country with a population of 1.26 billion
and to lead the people of different ethnic groups in pushing
forward the arduous modernization drive under complicated internal
and external circumstances, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The current and future competition in the world is,
fundamentally speaking, focused on the competition for talented
professionals, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Both history and current circumstances show that the success of
a nation and a political party largely relies on whether or not it
can foster outstanding and talented leaders, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
China's socialist cause will be consolidated and developed and
China will always stand invincible in the acute international
competition in the future so long as the CPC can constantly foster
a large number of highly qualified and talented leading officials,
he said.  
</P>
