<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0430 GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- A total of 109 banks in four European Union
countries were warned on Friday that investigation would be under
way for their cartel practices.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
bloc, released a list of these banks which have received
statements of objections in relation to a cartel investigation
into the fixing of charges for exchanging currencies in the euro
zone.
</P>
<P>
Such statements are a step in anti-trust proceedings but do not
pre-judge the final outcome of the investigation, commission
officials said. (EU-Banks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A U.S. jury in Miami ordered the tobacco industry
Friday to pay 145 billion dollars in punitive damages to sick
Florida smokers.
</P>
<P>
The six jurors, after a two-year trial of the case and hearing
157 witnesses, began deliberating the punitive damages question
Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
They deliberated less than five hours before making the record-
shattering verdict that the cigarette companies had claimed would
amount to a "death warrant."
</P>
<P>
This is the first class-action lawsuit against the tobacco
industry by smokers in the United States. (US-Jury-Smokers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The average price of Venezuelan oil for export stood
at 27.05 U.S. dollars per barrel July 10-14, a 1.71 dollar drop,
compared to the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
average price for its basket of crudes for export was quoted at 29.
35 dollars per barrel, and the price of the Brent crude was 30.73
dollars per barrel, 0.95 dollars and 9.82 dollars, respectively,
below the prices of the previous week, said the Mines and Energy
Ministry Friday. (Venezuela-Oil Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- Less than a year after the International
Telecommunication Union (ITU) signed a partnership agreement with
Geneva-based World Trade Center and WISeKey, deployment of e-
business infrastructure has started in more than 80 developing
countries, the ITU said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ITU Electronic Commerce for Developing Countries (EC-DC)
aims at enabling developing countries to use existing
infrastructures and services to join the digital economy through
non exclusive partnerships with the industry. (E Commerce-
Expansion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Chilean Finance Minister Nicolas Eyzaguirre said
Friday that his country does not need to raise its customs tariffs
for its admission as a Southern Common Market (Mercosur) full
member.
</P>
<P>
The minister said at the State of Sao Paulo Industries
Federation (FIESP) installations that the next step is to agree on
a calendar for the tariffs of the other countries of the bloc to
be reduced to Chile's level, now 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Eyzaguirre said that Chile will have, when it becomes a full
member of Mercosur, a term in which it will continue with an
autonomy regarding customs tariffs and freedom to negotiate trade
agreements with other countries or blocs, while the other Mercosur
countries are in the process of adjusting their tariffs. (Chile-
Mercosur-Tariffs) 
</P>
</TEXT>
