<HEADLINE> Greene Wins 100m in U.S. Olympic Trials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- World 100-meter record holder
Maurice Greene clocked 9.93 seconds at the U.S. Olympic trials in
Sacramento on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Greene's time was the second-fastest of the season, in his
qualifying race. After the race he promptly laid down a challenge
to 200-meter world record holder Michael Johnson, whom he will
meet over that distance in the trials next week.
</P>
<P>
"He thinks he's unbeatable, but you know who won the last race
we ran," said Greene, who defeated Johnson in the 1998 Prefontaine
Classic to even their record at 1-1.
</P>
<P>
While Greene still has semifinals and a final in the 100 meters
Saturday, he made it clear whom he really wanted to beat.
</P>
<P>
"Get Michael Johnson, that's what I want to do," Greene said.
</P>
</TEXT>
