<HEADLINE> THAI-SIA to Raise Airfares on Bangkok-Singapore Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Thai Airways International Plc. (
THAI), the national carrier, and Singapore Airlines (SIA), are
planning to jointly increase airfares on the Bangkok-Singapore
route, the Thai News Agency (TNA) said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
THAI director for Thailand Aran Apichart was quoted as saying
that THAI and SIA were discussing the new rates, as the two
national carriers had realized that they should not compete
against each other, but cooperate, because they had held a
combined market share of 70 percent on the route.
</P>
<P>
The two airlines were also discussing a shuttle flight service
with increased frequency, which will further help increase their
market share on the route, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
THAI and SIA together operate 12 flights a day on the Bangkok-
Singapore route; while other airlines, including Cathay Pacific,
Swissair, and SAS, offer a daily flight on the route, but charge
considerably less fares.
</P>
<P>
THAI is also negotiating with Cathay Pacific on the similar
form of cooperation on the Bangkok-Hong Kong route, the Thai
official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
