<HEADLINE> Polish MiG-21 Crashes, Killing Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A Polish MiG-21 fighter jet crashed
Friday during a routine sortie near Pila, Poznan Province, western
Poland, killing its pilot, Warsaw TV reported.
</P>
<P>
The pilot did not report what was wrong with the fighter before
the crash, the third involving Polish MiG-21s since 1999, the
television station said. The report did not give the cause of the
accident, but said such MiG-21 jets in Poland are obsolete.
</P>
<P>
Last May, a Polish MiG-21 fighter crashed in northern Poland
and its pilot survived. Five months later, another Polish MiG-21
jet crashed on the Baltic Coast shortly after its pilot ejected.
</P>
<P>
The country is looking to decommission more than 200 old-
fashioned MiG-21s as part of its drive to upgrade its defense
forces to meet standards required by NATO, which it joined last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
