<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Rocks Japan's Niijima Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A strong quake measuring 5.9 on the
Richter scale jolted Niijima Island and nearby islands south of
Tokyo on Saturday morning, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 10.30 a.m. (0130 GMT), was also
felt in various parts of eastern and central Japan including Tokyo,
Yokohama, Chiba and Nagano prefectures.
</P>
<P>
A landslide reportedly occurred in Niijima Island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
