<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin's Instruction on Party Building to Guide Cultural Work: Li Lanqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The remark on Party building made
by Chinese President Jiang Zemin early this year should serve to
guide the country's cultural work, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing has
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's instruction embodies the goals of the CPC, the essence
of socialism as well as the overall development demands of
politics, economy and culture in the course of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics, Li said this in a speech carried in
the latest issue of China's leading ideological magazine Seeking
Truth.
</P>
<P>
During his February tour of the southern province of Guangdong,
Jiang said that the key to running China well lies in the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC), in its ideology, style of work,
organization, discipline, capabilities and leadership.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will remain successful and enjoy the heartfelt support
of the people of China so long as the party always earnestly
represents the development requirements of China's advanced social
productive forces, the progressive course of China's advanced
culture, and the fundamental interests of the Chinese people,
noted Jiang, the top leader of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
For the country's cultural circles, it is imperative to fully
grasp the idea that the CPC always advocates the progressive
course of China's advanced culture, the vice-premier said in the
magazine article.
</P>
<P>
China's cultural circles should follow Jiang's instruction and
make their utmost contributions to the promotion of socialist
culture and to the overall economic and social progress, the vice-
premier stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
