<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Taiwan Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake, measuring 5.3 on
the Richter scale, jolted Hualien on the southeastern coast of
Taiwan early this morning, said information from the China
Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the earthquake took place at 07:04
hours (Beijing time) today, and the epicenter was located at 24.1
degrees north latitude and 121.6 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
Two earthquakes, one measuring 6.0 and the other measuring 5.3
on the Richter scale, also hit Taiwan's Hualien yesterday morning,
according to the China Seismological Bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
