<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Science News: Weekly Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
major science stories released by Xinhua last week:
</P>
<P>
Scientists Attach Importance to Ethical Issues in Genome Study
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists and experts here called on the whole of
society to pay attention to ethical issues in human genome
research and try to avoid negative effects of the research.
</P>
<P>
Human society is not fully prepared in the aspects of
psychology, ethics, law and international relations for the rapid
development of the Human Genome Project (HGP), which will bring
new risks and challenges to mankind, said Yang Huanming, a leading
scientist of the HGP in China.
</P>
<P>
China Develops Key Techniques for Largest Radio Telescope
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists have made breakthroughs in two key
techniques applied to build the world's largest radio telescope,
according to the Beijing Astronomical Observatory.
</P>
<P>
One of the techniques involves 2,000 pieces of metal to form
into a spherical surface for the radio telescope, with each piece
adjustable for keeping the direction and smoothness of the surface,
said Nan Rendong, chief scientist of the pre-research project.
</P>
<P>
China to Improve Meteorological Service for Western Region
</P>
<P>
Meteorological services in west China will be greatly improved
to minimize losses caused by natural disasters and to support
overall development in the region, promised the head of the China
Meteorological Administration..
</P>
<P>
"Modern meteorological technologies and equipment will be
introduced to combat the frequent and long-plaguing natural
disasters in the western region," said Wen Kegang.
</P>
<P>
Space Technology Exhibition Opens in Shanghai
</P>
<P>
A two-month exhibition on contemporary world astronautic
science, technology, and culture opened in Shanghai on July 9.
</P>
<P>
The mysterious spaceship Discovery, Apollo Moon Cabin, China's
Long March 4 carrier rocket and some other famous space navigation
tools are available on the show.
</P>
<P>
China's First Robot Manufacturing Company Set up
</P>
<P>
China's first robot development and production company was set
up in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, on
July 10.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the Siasun Robot &AMP; Automation Co. Ltd.
signifies the start of market-oriented industrial robot production
in China, said Wang Tianran, director of Shenyang Automation
Institute under the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
China to Turn Over 100 Large Scientific Research Organs Into
Ventures
</P>
<P>
China will convert over 100 large state-run scientific research
institutes attached to State Council ministries into ventures by
the end of this year, as a major step in the reform of the
research bodies.
</P>
<P>
A total of 242 of the state-run research organs were turned
into or merged with other ventures last year.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guanhua, Vice-Minister of Science and Technology, said on
July 10 at a national conference on reform of the institutes that
technological development research organs attached to the Ministry
of Construction, Ministry of Communications and some other
ministries are required to be turned into ventures.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
