<HEADLINE> S. African Ruling Party Urged Not to Lose Contact With Masses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
President Nelson Mandela Saturday urged his successor Thabo Mbeki
and other African National Congress (ANC) leaders to keep touch
with ordinary South Africans.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary for us to start talking about commitment to
the people. We must actually turn that into practice and go in the
areas that we stay and live. You will be surprised at the response,
" Mandela said at the last day of the ANC's national general
council.
</P>
<P>
The former president also focused on the ANC's call for a new
cadre, one imbued with the spirit of selflessness and voluntarism.
</P>
