rid of its careerists and opportunists.
</P>
<P>
The ANC's successes had nothing to do with "any particular
individual", but because of the efforts of the party's collective
leadership, he said, warning that individualism and factionalism
has taken root in party ranks.
</P>
<P>
He urged members to be loyal and to respect their leaders,
saying there were those outside the organization, including
opposition parties, who were trying to sow discord in the ANC.
</P>
<P>
Mandela said the need for a collective leadership was as
necessary today as during the past.
</P>
<P>
"We need the commitment of leaders at all levels in order to
achieve a better life for all that we promised our people," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to poverty, Mandela said, the ANC should not be
ashamed "in admitting that poverty is still with us."
</P>
<P>
