<HEADLINE> Ecuador To Have New Coins in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The new divisional coins will start
circulating in Ecuador by the first half of August, and the sucre
will disappear on September 13 as planned by the Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador entered in April a "dollarization" process that uses as
its basis the U.S. currency and relegates the sucre to
transactions with its fractions.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank opened Saturday a point of exchange in every
one of the biggest commercial centers of Lima and will do the same
in other similar sites next week.
</P>
<P>
A total of 562,000 dollars in divisional coins were put in
circulation during the first semester of the year to compensate
the retirement of the national small change.
</P>
<P>
Some 305 million dollars in bills were exchanged -- 148
million dollars have not been exchanged yet -- and 7.5 million
dollars in fractions of the U.S. currency, said the "El Comercio"
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The problem of the forgery of bills has grown with the start of
the dollar circulation in all commerce operations.
</P>
<P>
The "La Hora" newspaper Saturday quoted official sources as
saying that besides some confiscations by the authorities of
dollar forgeries, police detained this week in the border with
Colombia a citizen of that country who was traveling to Quito in
an autobus with 52,000 dollars in falsified bills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
