integrating all the economies of the region, but must also try to
insert itself into the Free Trade Association of the Americas (
FTAA).
</P>
<P>
Pettigrew also said that it is necessary to work hard for the
projected FTAA to be completed in 2005.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian minister said at the end of his visit that his
government plans to increase the present level of trade with
Uruguay and acknowledged the commitment of this country with the
FTAA development.
</P>
<P>
