<HEADLINE> Eight Peasants Killed in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Eight rural workers have been
killed in two communities of the Zona Bananera municipality in the
north of Colombia, mayor of that town Jesus Alberto Avendano said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Five of the victims were riddled with bullets Friday by unknown
attackers in the Guacamayal community, and the other three in the
Sopladoe locality.
</P>
<P>
One of the dead was identified as municipal council president
Edelberto Aguilar, who according to Avendano, was taken out of his
house and assassinated in the town's plaza.
</P>
<P>
Community members accused right-win paramilitary groups for the
eight deaths, but Avendano said he does not know who they are.
</P>
<P>
The People's Defenders said in a report published this week
that 235 massacres were committed in Colombia during the first
semester of 2000 with a result of 1,073 victims.  
</P>
</TEXT>
